<paragraph blockId="1.[199,1315,152,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">
The new species is similar to 
<emphasis box="[514,695,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">C. n. nigrocornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[702,847,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" refId="ref1266" refString="Walker, F. (1870) Catalogue of the Specimens of Dermaptera Saltatoria in the Collection of the British Museum. Printed for the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 791 pp." type="book" year="1870">Walker, 1870</bibRefCitation>
. The major differences are listed in 
<tableCitation box="[1229,1309,152,175]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,152,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of Ceracris jianfenglingensis sp. nov. and C. n. nigrocornis Walker, 1870" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Table 1</tableCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Etymology</emphasis>
: The specific epithet is named for the 
<typeStatus box="[732,778,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">type</typeStatus>
locality Jianfengling Mountain.
</paragraph>
